@person
Feature: Create a new person through PUT and get appropriate response
	Scenario: client makes call to PUT /test/person
		When the client calls /test/person
		Then the client receives PUT status code of 200
		And the client receives person name Charlie
		And the client receives person age 32
		And the client receives person email charlie@gmail.com
		And the client receives person has 2 friends
		And the client receives person's second friend is named Bob
